Shipments of diamonds from  Sierra
Leone  climbed 25 percent to 41,880 carats in June compared with
33,450 carats a month earlier, the West African nationâ€™s central
bank said in an economic review.  Gold exports rose to 551,500 ounces in June from 549,790
ounces in May, the Freetown-based Bank of Sierra Leone said in
an e-mailed report today.  Total diamond shipments were 204,890 carats for the six
months through June, Joseph Pessima, a senior economist at the
central bank, said by phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
